Subclasses can use the protected AbstractTransformer.input field to retrieve the ID in an implementation-dependent way.

      • messagePrefix

        protected String messagePrefix()
        Description copied from class: AbstractTransformer
        A standard prefix for all messages logged using one of the specialized log methods in this class. The idea is that any message is by default prefixed with the ID of the object for which the message was generated. By default the message prefix is a right-padded column containing the object ID of the validated object. Therefore, one of the first things subclasses must do in their implementation of transform() is set the AbstractTransformer.objectID field. Subclasses may override messagePrefix() if appropriate.
        Overrides:
        messagePrefix in class AbstractTransformer<XMLRecordInfo,nl.naturalis.nda.elasticsearch.dao.estypes.ESMultiMediaObject>
        Returns:
        See Also:
        AbstractTransformer.error(String, Object...), AbstractTransformer.warn(String, Object...), AbstractTransformer.info(String, Object...), AbstractTransformer.debug(String, Object...)

      • skipRecord

        protected boolean skipRecord()
        Description copied from class: AbstractTransformer
        Whether or not to skip the current record. By default all records are processed, but subclasses can override this method to discard records before they are even handed over to the AbstractTransformer.doTransform() method. They can use the protected AbstractTransformer.input field to determine if the record should be skipped.
        Overrides:
